    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>NBC in Sydney: The Judges Frown</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bill Valentine letter says NBC analysts should stop their incessant chattering and let beauty of Olympic performances speak for themselves (Sept 20 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''NBC's Ratings for Olympics Are Worst Ever'' (front page, Sept. 20):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''NBC's Ratings for Olympics Are Worst Ever'' (front page, Sept. 20):</p>
        <p>Add this to the long list of reasons not to watch the Olympics: the incessant, adolescent chattering of the analysts NBC hires from the ranks of former athletes. They seem obsessed with the athletes' mistakes and shortcomings and measure all things by one standard: the pursuit of gold.</p>
        <p>Since we already know who has won, the analysts should be quiet and let us enjoy the beauty of the performance itself.</p>
        <p>BILL VALENTINE  New York, Sept. 20, 2000</p>
      </block>
